# Changelog

All notable changes to the Chatbot Integration Plugin will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [1.0.0] - 2024-01-01

### Added
- Initial plugin release
- Support for 7 major chatbot providers:
  - Crisp Chat
  - Tidio Live Chat  
  - WhatsApp Business
  - Facebook Messenger
  - LiveChat
  - Zendesk Chat
  - Tawk.to
- Comprehensive admin interface for configuration management
- Real-time connection testing for all providers
- Database logging system for events and debugging
- Automatic frontend theme integration
- Webhook handling system
- Provider-specific configuration schemas
- Bulk actions for managing multiple chatbots
- SOLID principle architecture with Laravel 10 standards
- Comprehensive documentation and API reference

### Features
- **Multiple Provider Management**: Configure and manage multiple chatbot providers from a single interface
- **Automatic Script Injection**: Seamless integration with existing Twig themes without manual code changes
- **Connection Testing**: Built-in testing to verify provider configurations
- **Logging & Monitoring**: Track events, errors, and webhook activities
- **Flexible Configuration**: Provider-specific settings with validation
- **Theme Integration**: Works with existing TechGuru theme system
- **Security**: All inputs sanitized and validated according to security best practices
- **Extensible**: Easy to add new chatbot providers following the established pattern

### Technical Implementation
- Laravel 10 compatible with strict typing
- PSR-12 coding standards
- Database migrations for configuration and logging tables
- Service provider pattern for dependency injection
- Manager pattern for provider handling
- Interface-based provider architecture
- Comprehensive error handling and logging
- RESTful API endpoints for webhooks

### Documentation
- Complete README with installation and configuration instructions
- API reference documentation
- Provider-specific configuration guides
- Troubleshooting section
- Extension guidelines for custom providers

## [Unreleased]

### Planned Features
- Additional chatbot providers (Intercom, Drift, etc.)
- Advanced analytics and reporting
- Custom chatbot themes and styling
- Multi-language support
- Integration with CRM systems
- A/B testing capabilities
- Performance optimization
- Mobile app integration

---

For more detailed information about each release, please refer to the [README.md](README.md) file. 